<TITLE> New home loan scheme takes effect from Nov 1 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 31 (bdnews24.com)  Home buyers can now borrow up to Tk 40 lakh at 12 percent simple interest, with a 20 percent down payment, and a repayment period of five to 15 years, the Bangladesh House Building Finance Corporation said Wednesday. The BHBFC's loan policy for 2007 will target middle and lower middle home buyers. The new policy which the BHBFC says is simpler and more pragmatic than its predecessor and will be in effect on a limited scale in Dhaka and Chittagong from Nov 1. Loans will be subject to appraisals of property location, probable rent, applicant's monthly income, other sources of income, and the applicant's status. bd
